        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 6:56PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 655 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Decatur, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Van Wert, Decatur, Delphos, Paulding, Antwerp, Monroeville, Payne,
Convoy, Ohio City, Middlebury, Middle Point, Dixon, Grover Hill,
Willshire, Scott, Haviland, Wren, Latty, Venedocia, and Broughton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
